===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|i}}: a [[horizontal]] [[stroke]], indicating the number {{m-g|[[one]]}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=壹-financial,弌-ancient,𠤪,𭍶}}
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ʔit}}. Descendants from the {{m|sit-pro|*ʔit}} etymon account for the majority of the dialectal forms for “one” in Chinese (Mandarin, Jin, Gan, Hakka, Hui, Xiang, Yue, Wu groups, etc.).

